UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. TAKARA LABORATORIES, Appellee. No. 9047. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 19, 1938. Carl C. Donaugh, U. S. Atty., and M. B. Strayer, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Portland, Or. Robert C. Bradshaw, of Portland, Or., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellant, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
